This paper is about natural language processing (NLP) and transfer learning, which are both subfields of computer science. The paper specifically focuses on adapting a method called Universal Language Model for Fine-tuning (ULMFiT) to the Polish language using subword tokenization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which could fall under categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions that their approach involves convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
